This paper is about on-device image recognition using convolutional neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the development of a new neural network architecture, which is a topic that falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the model on landmark databases, which is a topic that falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
